♪

2
00:01:06,687 --> 00:01:10,173
[brushing on canvas]

3
00:01:28,847 --> 00:01:32,195
[brushing on canvas]

4
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:20,209
- [baby cooing]

5
00:02:26,387 --> 00:02:29,666
- AW...
[laughs]

6
00:02:35,396 --> 00:02:39,918
OK. OH...

7
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:42,300
- [cooing]

8
00:02:42,334 --> 00:02:44,750
- OOH, MY LITTLE MAN.
YES, YES, YES.

9
00:02:44,785 --> 00:02:48,720
[kissing sounds]

10
00:02:48,754 --> 00:02:50,756
[laughs]

11
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:54,208
[cars honking]

12
00:02:59,765 --> 00:03:02,768
[classical music]

13
00:03:06,703 --> 00:03:09,879
- BRITT, WHERE WERE YOU
LAST NIGHT? WE MISSED YOU.

14
00:03:09,913 --> 00:03:12,295
EVERYONE ASKED FOR YOU.

15
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:13,917
- WEREN'T YOU THE ONE
WHO TOLD ME

16
00:03:13,952 --> 00:03:15,781
THAT I HAD TO BUILD
MY BODY OF WORK?

17
00:03:15,816 --> 00:03:18,612
I WAS HOME WORKING.

18
00:03:18,646 --> 00:03:20,855
- NICHOLAS SAID YOU WERE
UPSET ABOUT SOMETHING.

19
00:03:20,890 --> 00:03:24,307
- NO. I'M FINE.

20
00:03:28,966 --> 00:03:33,005
- YOU KNOW, I RAISED TWO KIDSON MY OWN RIGHT HERE.

21
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:36,630
THEY'D CRAWL AROUND THE FLOORBETWEEN THE LEGS OF THE ARTISTS

22
00:03:36,664 --> 00:03:39,942
AND CLIMB IN MY LAP WHILE I WAS
TALKING TO INVESTORS.

23
00:03:39,978 --> 00:03:42,774
IT WAS A GREAT EXPERIENCE.

24
00:03:42,808 --> 00:03:47,848
- I-- THIS KID IS--
HE'S A GIFT.

25
00:03:47,882 --> 00:03:49,298
IT'S JUST HARD, YOU KNOW.

26
00:03:54,958 --> 00:03:56,926
- I'VE RECOMMENDED YOU
FOR THE ARTIST ACADEMY

27
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:57,996
FOUNDATION GRANT.

28
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:59,860
- YOU WHAT?

29
00:03:59,894 --> 00:04:02,863
- IT'S WORTH $25,000
IF THEY ACCEPT YOU,

30
00:04:02,897 --> 00:04:04,865
AND, OF COURSE,
A MAJOR EXHIBITION.

31
00:04:04,899 --> 00:04:08,075
- [sniffs]
[sighs]

32
00:04:08,109 --> 00:04:10,974
[birds tweeting]

33
00:04:30,856 --> 00:04:32,064
- MORNING, MAMA.

34
00:04:32,099 --> 00:04:35,861
- OH, GOOD MORNING.
[laughs]

35
00:04:35,896 --> 00:04:37,863
[kissing sounds]
- READY FOR BREAKFAST?

36
00:04:37,898 --> 00:04:40,452
- OH, DARLING, I'VE MADEA DECISION ABOUT THANKSGIVING.

37
00:04:40,487 --> 00:04:42,040
- OH, GOOD. WHERE DO I
MAKE A RESERVATION?

38
00:04:42,074 --> 00:04:45,871
- NO, NO, NO.
I'M GOING TO COOK.

39
00:04:45,906 --> 00:04:47,908
- ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO THAT?

40
00:04:47,942 --> 00:04:49,703
- ABSOLUTELY.

41
00:04:49,737 --> 00:04:51,498
NOW, WILL YOU BE A PEACH
AND CALL CONNIE AND MERLE,

42
00:04:51,532 --> 00:04:53,914
BECAUSE I HAVE SO MANY THINGSTO DO.

43
00:04:53,948 --> 00:04:57,055
OH, CALL BRITT.

44
00:04:57,089 --> 00:04:59,057
- WHY DON'T YOU CALL BRITT?

45
00:04:59,091 --> 00:05:02,336
- I THINK IT WOULD BE BETTER
IF YOU DID.

46
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:10,724
[phone rings]

47
00:05:13,899 --> 00:05:16,832
[phone rings]

48
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:23,909
[phone rings]

49
00:05:23,944 --> 00:05:25,463
- HELLO?

50
00:05:25,497 --> 00:05:28,017
- BRITT, IS THAT YOU?
- BARELY.

51
00:05:28,051 --> 00:05:30,088
- DID I WAKE YOU?
- WHAT TIME IS IT?

52
00:05:30,122 --> 00:05:31,538
- IT'S TWO IN THE AFTERNOON.

53
00:05:31,572 --> 00:05:35,024
- I WAS JUST NAPPING
WITH HENRY.

54
00:05:35,058 --> 00:05:39,062
WHAT IS GOING ON, VALETTA?
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

55
00:05:39,097 --> 00:05:40,892
- OF COURSE, EVERYTHING'S
ALL RIGHT.

56
00:05:40,926 --> 00:05:43,481
I-- I JUST HAVEN'T HAD
A MINUTE TO CHECK IN ON YOU.

57
00:05:43,515 --> 00:05:46,034
I-- YOU KNOW HOW IT IS HERE.
I'VE BEEN VERY BUSY.

58
00:05:46,069 --> 00:05:50,488
ALWAYS LOTS GOING ON.JULIAN HAS HIS BUSINESS DINNERS.

59
00:05:50,522 --> 00:05:52,455
I'M PICKING PEOPLE UP,
DROPPING THEM OFF.

60
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:57,598
CUB SCOUTS.DAUGHTERS OF AMERICA MEETINGS.

61
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:58,944
UM...

62
00:05:58,979 --> 00:06:02,914
I'M AT MAMA'S.
- AND HOW IS MAGGIE?

63
00:06:02,948 --> 00:06:04,536
- OH, SHE'S FINE.

64
00:06:04,571 --> 00:06:06,158
- SO, WHAT ARE YOU TRYING
TO SAY, VALETTA?

65
00:06:06,193 --> 00:06:10,473
- THANKSGIVING'S COMING UP.
- YEAH?

66
00:06:10,508 --> 00:06:11,957
- SO SHE WANTS ALL OF US HERE.

67
00:06:11,992 --> 00:06:13,994
- YEAH.

68
00:06:14,028 --> 00:06:17,446
- MAMA SAYS SHE'S GOING TO
FIX DINNER HERSELF.

69
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,965
- IT WOULD ALMOST BE WORTH
COMING TO SEE THAT.

70
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,933
- BRITT, YOU KNOW HOW LONG IT'S
BEEN SINCE YOU'VE BEEN HERE?

71
00:06:21,967 --> 00:06:26,731
- OK. I'LL THINK ABOUT IT, OK?

72
00:06:26,765 --> 00:06:29,147
- GOOD.

73
00:06:29,181 --> 00:06:31,149
WE'LL SEE YOU THEN.

74
00:06:31,183 --> 00:06:33,151
- I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

75
00:06:33,185 --> 00:06:36,603
AND, UH, VALETTA?
- YES?

76
00:06:36,637 --> 00:06:38,190
- THANK YOU FOR
THE WAKE UP CALL.

77
00:06:38,225 --> 00:06:41,124
- ANYTIME.
[beeps off]

78
00:06:43,195 --> 00:06:46,026
[sirens wailing]

79
00:06:59,246 --> 00:07:02,663
- YOU HAVE GOT STRONG HANDS.

80
00:07:02,698 --> 00:07:04,665
- BABY, THESE ARE MORE LIKE
WORN IN.

81
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,978
- [laughs]
OH, NO.

82
00:07:07,012 --> 00:07:09,187
IT'S REALLY BEAUTIFUL.

83
00:07:09,221 --> 00:07:11,534
- I KNEW I LIKED HAVING YOU
AROUND.

84
00:07:11,569 --> 00:07:14,503
YOU'RE AN EASY AUDIENCE
TO PLEASE.

85
00:07:14,537 --> 00:07:16,159
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
I'D DO WITHOUT YOU.

86
00:07:16,194 --> 00:07:18,161
- YOU KIDDING ME? IF I DIDN'THAVE YOU TO LOOK AFTER HENRY...

87
00:07:18,196 --> 00:07:20,681
- HEY, WHAT DID I TELL YOU?

88
00:07:20,716 --> 00:07:22,959
THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS DO
FOR ONE ANOTHER.

89
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:26,653
[knocking]

90
00:07:26,687 --> 00:07:28,793
- I'LL GET IT.
IT'S PROBABLY NICHOLAS.

91
00:07:35,731 --> 00:07:37,042
- HI.
- HEY.

92
00:07:37,077 --> 00:07:38,216
- SORRY I'M LATE.
- IT'S OK.

93
00:07:41,081 --> 00:07:42,945
HE'S SLEEPING,
AND I ALREADY FED HIM.

94
00:07:42,979 --> 00:07:45,637
- GOOD.

95
00:07:45,672 --> 00:07:48,226
HMM. I'LL TAKE HIM
TO THE STUDIO.

96
00:07:50,228 --> 00:07:52,575
HEY, HENRY.
HOW'S MY BOY?

97
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:54,232
- HEY, NICHOLAS.
HOW YOU DOING, MAN?

98
00:07:54,266 --> 00:07:55,647
YOU WANT SOMETHING TO DRINK?

99
00:07:55,682 --> 00:07:59,582
- NO, THANKS, MARION. NO.

100
00:07:59,617 --> 00:08:01,032
CAN I TALK TO YOU
OUTSIDE FOR A MINUTE?

101
00:08:01,066 --> 00:08:03,137
- YEAH.

102
00:08:03,172 --> 00:08:05,830
- GO AHEAD.I GOT EVERYTHING COVERED HERE.

103
00:08:08,557 --> 00:08:10,593
- SO, HAVE YOU THOUGHT
ABOUT US AT ALL?

104
00:08:10,628 --> 00:08:13,113
- ACTUALLY, VERY LITTLE.
- THAT'S FUNNY.

105
00:08:13,147 --> 00:08:15,046
- [laughs]

106
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,875
- SERIOUSLY,

107
00:08:16,910 --> 00:08:18,912
THERE'S SOMEONE ELSE TO CONSIDERIN ALL THIS, YOU KNOW.

108
00:08:18,946 --> 00:08:21,086
- YEAH, HENRY AND I
ARE GETTING ALONG JUST FINE.

109
00:08:21,121 --> 00:08:25,090
- I KNOW YOU'RE FINE,
BUT HE NEEDS A FATHER.

110
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:27,230
- HE'S GOT A FATHER-- YOU.

111
00:08:27,265 --> 00:08:28,749
- OK, YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

112
00:08:28,784 --> 00:08:30,268
- DO WE REALLY NEED TO
DO THIS AGAIN?

113
00:08:32,719 --> 00:08:35,722
- I WANT YOU, BRITT.
I WANT MY SON.

114
00:08:35,756 --> 00:08:38,102
I WANT TO BE LIKE
A REAL FAMILY.

115
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:42,107
- I LOVE YOU.
I DO.

116
00:08:45,076 --> 00:08:47,872
I CAN'T TALK ABOUT THIS NOW.

117
00:08:53,602 --> 00:08:56,294
AND MY MOTHER WANTS METO COME HOME FOR THANKSGIVING,

118
00:08:56,328 --> 00:08:58,227
SO IF I GO,
I'M GOING TO BRING HENRY.

119
00:08:58,261 --> 00:08:59,711
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

120
00:08:59,746 --> 00:09:02,231
- WELL, THAT'S GOOD.
THAT'S VERY GOOD.

121
00:09:02,265 --> 00:09:05,234
WANT ME TO GO WITH YOU?
- [laughs] OH, NO.

122
00:09:05,268 --> 00:09:07,892
I CARE ABOUT YOU WAY TOO MUCHTO SUBJECT YOU TO MY MOTHER.

123
00:09:07,926 --> 00:09:10,273
- MM.

124
00:09:10,308 --> 00:09:12,310
YOU NEED SOME MONEY?

125
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:14,312
I MEAN, I SOLD A COUPLE
PAINTINGS THE OTHER DAY.

126
00:09:14,346 --> 00:09:15,658
I--I'M ABLE TO HELP, YOU KNOW.

127
00:09:15,693 --> 00:09:18,074
- I DON'T NEED ANYTHING.
I'M FINE.

128
00:09:18,109 --> 00:09:19,248
- CAN I CALL YOU
WHEN YOU'RE THERE?

129
00:09:19,282 --> 00:09:21,319
- I DIDN'T SAY I'M GOING.

130
00:09:24,115 --> 00:09:25,323
[cutting sounds]

131
00:09:31,743 --> 00:09:34,159
- I SURE HOPE BRITT SHOWS UP.

132
00:09:34,194 --> 00:09:35,782
IT WILL BE THE FIRST
REAL THANKSGIVING

133
00:09:35,816 --> 00:09:37,611
WE'VE HAD IN YEARS.

134
00:09:37,646 --> 00:09:42,167
- REMIND ME, WHICH SIDE OF THEKNIFE DOES THE SPOON GO ON.

135
00:09:45,308 --> 00:09:50,141
- IT GOES ON THE OUTSIDE.
KNIFE PROTECTS THE SPOON.

136
00:09:50,175 --> 00:09:51,798
[stirring]

137
00:09:51,832 --> 00:09:53,351
SIT DOWN BECAUSE
HERE IT COMES.

138
00:09:57,148 --> 00:09:59,184
- MMM. LOOKS GREAT.

139
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:03,844
DON'T YOU EVER GET TIRED OF

140
00:10:03,879 --> 00:10:05,121
TAKING CARE OF
YOUR SISTER-IN-LAW?

141
00:10:05,156 --> 00:10:07,434
- WELL, YEAH,

142
00:10:07,468 --> 00:10:09,988
BUT WHO ELSE HAS THE PATIENCETO DEAL WITH YOU?

143
00:10:10,023 --> 00:10:14,268
- [laughs]

144
00:10:14,303 --> 00:10:15,200
[liquid pouring]

145
00:10:17,824 --> 00:10:19,688
[car honking]

146
00:10:35,186 --> 00:10:36,981
[plane landing]

147
00:10:39,362 --> 00:10:45,368
[tires screeching]

148
00:10:47,336 --> 00:10:53,135
[muted overhead announcements]

149
00:11:18,436 --> 00:11:20,196
- WE'RE HERE.

150
00:11:23,441 --> 00:11:25,339
- BRITT!

151
00:11:25,374 --> 00:11:27,341
OH, FINALLY!
- HEY.

152
00:11:27,376 --> 00:11:30,137
- I'VE JUST BEEN WAITINGAND WAITING FOR YOU TO GET HERE.

153
00:11:30,172 --> 00:11:32,864
- OH.
- OH.

154
00:11:32,899 --> 00:11:35,453
OOH, THIN AS A STICK.
- OH, PLEASE!

155
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:37,455
- DON'T THEY FEED YOU
IN THE BIG CITY?

156
00:11:37,489 --> 00:11:39,906
- I EAT LIKE A PIG.
- WHERE'S THAT KID?

157
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:41,942
both: [laughing]

158
00:11:41,977 --> 00:11:43,426
- HENRY?

159
00:11:43,461 --> 00:11:44,945
THERE WE GO.

160
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:47,810
[sighs]
THIS IS HENRY.

161
00:11:47,845 --> 00:11:50,917
- WHAT A HANDSOME DEVIL
YOU ARE.

162
00:11:50,951 --> 00:11:52,539
- MEET YOUR AUNT BILLY

163
00:11:52,573 --> 00:11:54,886
WHO'S GOING TO BE ON HER
BEST BEHAVIOR, AREN'T YOU?

164
00:11:54,921 --> 00:11:57,440
- NOT A GHOST OF A CHANCE.
[laughs]

165
00:11:57,475 --> 00:12:00,927
HEY, COME ON.
LET'S GO INSIDE.

166
00:12:00,961 --> 00:12:02,445
- I'LL GET THE BAGS.

167
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,447
- NO, LEAVE 'EM.
I'LL GET 'EM LATER.

168
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:14,147
WELL, HENRY, HERE WE ARE.
HOME.

169
00:12:14,181 --> 00:12:16,356
[laughs]

170
00:12:16,390 --> 00:12:18,254
WHY DON'T YOU COME
IN THE KITCHEN WITH ME.

171
00:12:18,289 --> 00:12:21,223
I'VE GOT SOMETHING
REALLY GOOD FOR YOU.

172
00:12:21,257 --> 00:12:22,293
[laughs]

173
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:29,749
WE SURE ARE GLAD YOU'RE HOME
WHERE YOU BELONG, KIDDO.

174
00:12:34,339 --> 00:12:39,241
OK, HERE YOU ARE
IN AUNT BILLY'S KITCHEN.

175
00:12:39,275 --> 00:12:41,484
[buckles clinking]

176
00:12:48,422 --> 00:12:51,598
- CAREFUL. DON'T HACK THE LIMBS.CUT THEM.

177
00:12:51,632 --> 00:12:54,221
I DON'T WANT THEM LOOKING
ALL CHOPPED UP.

178
00:12:57,638 --> 00:12:59,502
- YOU SHOULD HAVE BEEN
A GENERAL.

179
00:12:59,537 --> 00:13:01,781
PATTON WOULD HAVE WORSHIPPED
AT YOUR FEET.

180
00:13:04,404 --> 00:13:07,407
- [laughs]

181
00:13:07,441 --> 00:13:10,859
HELLO THERE.
- HEY.

182
00:13:10,893 --> 00:13:13,413
- HOW DID YOU GET HERE?
- TOOK A CAB.

183
00:13:13,447 --> 00:13:15,415
- WELL, WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ANYONE?

184
00:13:15,449 --> 00:13:17,417
I WOULD HAVE HAD YOU PICKED UP.
- OH.

185
00:13:17,451 --> 00:13:19,350
- IS HENRY WITH YOU?
- YEAH, HENRY'S WITH ME.

186
00:13:19,384 --> 00:13:21,490
- BRITT, YOU TOOK A CAB
WITH A BABY?

187
00:13:21,524 --> 00:13:23,526
- YEAH.

188
00:13:23,561 --> 00:13:24,976
- YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THOSE DRIVERS.

189
00:13:25,011 --> 00:13:26,426
THE CABS ARE FILTHY.

190
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:27,427
A GIRL'S NOT SAFE
IN ONE OF THOSE THINGS.

191
00:13:27,461 --> 00:13:29,291
- VALETTA.
- NO.

192
00:13:29,325 --> 00:13:30,395
WHEN JULIAN AND I GO
TO THE AIRPORT,

193
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:31,949
WE ALWAYS HIRE A LIMO.

194
00:13:31,983 --> 00:13:34,503
- OK, FINE.
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?

195
00:13:34,537 --> 00:13:37,955
- I'M TRYING TO GET THIS PLACEINTO SOME SORT OF SHAPE.

196
00:13:37,989 --> 00:13:39,404
[sighs]

197
00:13:39,439 --> 00:13:40,612
MAMA DOESN'T WANT TO
SPEND ANY MONEY ON IT,

198
00:13:40,647 --> 00:13:41,855
AND IT'S GETTING RUNDOWN.

199
00:13:41,890 --> 00:13:43,546
I MEAN, HERE IT IS NOVEMBER.

200
00:13:43,581 --> 00:13:45,307
ALL OF THIS SHOULD HAVE
BEEN DONE MONTHS AGO.

201
00:13:45,341 --> 00:13:47,205
- LOOK'S PRETTY GOOD TO ME.

202
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,551
- THAT'S BECAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

203
00:13:48,586 --> 00:13:50,243
IT'S IN TERRIBLE CONDITION.

204
00:13:50,277 --> 00:13:52,935
THE HOUSE NEEDS PAINT
AND A MILLION OTHER THINGS.

205
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:57,491
SHE JUST HAS NO IDEA WHAT NEEDS
TO BE DONE AROUND HERE.

206
00:13:57,526 --> 00:13:58,976
- HOW IS MAGGIE?

207
00:13:59,010 --> 00:14:02,048
- YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
TO SEE HER YET?

208
00:14:02,082 --> 00:14:05,085
UH, SHE'S GOOD.

209
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,881
SHE'S OVER THERE
WORKING IN HER FLOWER BEDS.

210
00:14:07,916 --> 00:14:11,402
- SO, UM, YOU GOING TO
BE HERE FOR A WHILE?

211
00:14:11,436 --> 00:14:13,093
- NO, I AM OUT OF HERE

212
00:14:13,128 --> 00:14:14,888
AS SOON AS I CAN GET THESE GUYS
TO FINISH UP.

213
00:14:14,923 --> 00:14:16,614
LITTLE JULIAN HAS
PIANO PRACTICE.

214
00:14:16,648 --> 00:14:19,065
BUT WE'RE ALL COMING FOR DINNER.- OH, OK.

215
00:14:19,099 --> 00:14:21,032
THEN I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
- MM-HMM.

216
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:23,103
UH, BRITT?

217
00:14:23,138 --> 00:14:25,416
DON'T FORGET TO DRESS
FOR DINNER.

218
00:14:25,450 --> 00:14:28,453
- [laughs]

219
00:14:30,593 --> 00:14:33,389
OK. DRESS FOR DINNER.

220
00:14:33,424 --> 00:14:35,495
RIGHT.

221
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,601
- [sighs]

222
00:14:47,610 --> 00:14:48,888
- MAGGIE?

223
00:14:53,064 --> 00:14:54,928
- BRITT.

224
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:02,625
IT SEEMS LIKE FOREVER.

225
00:15:04,731 --> 00:15:06,664
YOU COULD HAVE CALLED
NOW AND THEN.

226
00:15:06,698 --> 00:15:09,356
- SO COULD YOU.

227
00:15:16,674 --> 00:15:21,437
- NOW LET ME GET A LOOK AT YOU.

228
00:15:21,472 --> 00:15:23,439
YOU'RE PENCIL THIN.

229
00:15:25,441 --> 00:15:27,064
- YOU'RE LOOKING WELL.

230
00:15:27,098 --> 00:15:29,411
- [laughs]

231
00:15:29,445 --> 00:15:32,655
THESE WRINKLES KEEP MULTIPLYING
LIKE HOUSEFLIES.

232
00:15:32,690 --> 00:15:35,072
GROWING OLD IS FOR THE BIRDS.

233
00:15:35,106 --> 00:15:37,108
- IT'S HARD FOR ME TO
IMAGINE YOU OLD.

234
00:15:37,143 --> 00:15:39,283
- WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE
I WON'T GIVE INTO IT.

235
00:15:39,317 --> 00:15:41,112
[laughs]

236
00:15:41,147 --> 00:15:43,563
YOUR FATHER AND I USED TO
BE OUT HERE FOR HOURS AND HOURS

237
00:15:43,597 --> 00:15:45,565
WITH ALL THESE LEAVES FALLING.

238
00:15:45,599 --> 00:15:47,567
WE'D BE RAKING UNTIL
OUR BACKS WERE ACHING.

239
00:15:47,601 --> 00:15:49,327
[laughs]

240
00:15:49,362 --> 00:15:52,641
YES, I'M GOING TO PLANT
ZINNIAS HERE THIS SPRING.

241
00:15:52,675 --> 00:15:54,677
IT WAS YOUR FATHER'S
FAVORITE FLOWER, YOU KNOW.

242
00:16:01,132 --> 00:16:03,272
- SO HOW YOU BEEN FEELING?

243
00:16:06,068 --> 00:16:08,174
- PEOPLE MAKE SUCH A FUSS
ABOUT GETTING OLD.

244
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:09,658
THAT'S ALL THEY EVER
WANT TO TALK ABOUT.

245
00:16:09,692 --> 00:16:11,798
NEXT SUBJECT.

246
00:16:11,832 --> 00:16:13,765
- WHY DO WE HAVE TO
CHANGE THE SUBJECT?

247
00:16:16,492 --> 00:16:19,702
- I DON'T WANT TO MAKE THIS
HOLIDAY INTO A WAR ZONE, BRITT.

248
00:16:19,737 --> 00:16:21,428
DO WE UNDERSTAND ONE ANOTHER?

249
00:16:23,223 --> 00:16:24,673
- I DIDN'T START ANYTHING.

250
00:16:24,707 --> 00:16:27,641
- DO WE UNDERSTAND ONE ANOTHER?

251
00:16:27,676 --> 00:16:29,712
- I'M GOING TO GO CHECK
ON HENRY.

252
00:16:29,747 --> 00:16:32,681
- IS THAT YOUR BOYFRIEND?

253
00:16:32,715 --> 00:16:36,478
- NO, IT'S MY SON, REMEMBER?

254
00:16:36,512 --> 00:16:40,171
- OH, CHARLIE WAS SO HANDSOME.

255
00:16:40,206 --> 00:16:42,001
- WHAT DOES DADDY
HAVE TO DO WITH THIS?

256
00:16:51,734 --> 00:16:55,635
- WELL, WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT THE OLD PLACE?

257
00:16:55,669 --> 00:16:57,740
- NOTHING SEEMS TO CHANGE.

258
00:17:01,606 --> 00:17:03,712
WANT TO COME MEET
YOUR GRANDSON?

259
00:17:03,746 --> 00:17:06,611
- WELL, NO. I'LL MEET HIM
AT DINNER, DEAR.

260
00:18:06,257 --> 00:18:07,603
[cell phone rings]

261
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:11,780
- HELLO?

262
00:18:11,814 --> 00:18:13,713
- CLAIRE GOODMAN EISENBERG,

263
00:18:13,747 --> 00:18:15,232
HAVE YOU BECOME
A BORING OLD BITTY?

264
00:18:15,266 --> 00:18:17,303
- [laughs]BRITT, WHERE THE HECK ARE YOU?

265
00:18:17,337 --> 00:18:21,134
- [laughs]
I AM RIGHT HERE AT HOME.

266
00:18:21,169 --> 00:18:24,172
- OH MY, HENRY.
IS HE WONDERFUL?

267
00:18:24,206 --> 00:18:28,693
- HENRY'S BEAUTIFUL.
HE'S...HE'S BEAUTIFUL.

268
00:18:28,728 --> 00:18:29,798
- OK, I HAVE TO SEE YOU.

269
00:18:29,832 --> 00:18:32,180
- TOMORROW?
- PERFECT.

270
00:18:32,214 --> 00:18:34,320
UH, GET YOUR BEHIND OUT HERE
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING,

271
00:18:34,354 --> 00:18:35,321
AND WEAR YOUR BOOTS.

272
00:18:35,355 --> 00:18:36,805
- SEE YA.

273
00:18:36,839 --> 00:18:38,393
[clicks off phone]

274
00:18:38,427 --> 00:18:39,463
[sighs]

275
00:19:00,863 --> 00:19:03,590
- WE'LL TALK ABOUT THIS LATER.

276
00:19:06,697 --> 00:19:09,148
COME ON, SWEETIE.

277
00:19:15,878 --> 00:19:18,329
- [cooing]
- HEY, BRITT. LONG TIME NO SEE.

278
00:19:18,364 --> 00:19:19,606
- [laughs]
HEY, JULIAN.

279
00:19:19,641 --> 00:19:23,300
- OH, MY GOODNESS.
- LOOK AT HIM.

280
00:19:23,334 --> 00:19:26,648
- OH MY GOODNESS! HELLO!
[kissing sounds]

281
00:19:26,682 --> 00:19:30,307
OH, WHAT A BEAUTIFUL BOY.

282
00:19:30,341 --> 00:19:32,378
- WELL, HE HAS YOUR EYES.

283
00:19:32,412 --> 00:19:34,345
- I THINK THEY'RE NICHOLAS'S.

284
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:36,278
- WHERE IS THIS NICHOLAS
ANYWAY?

285
00:19:36,313 --> 00:19:37,900
- HE'S IN L.A.

286
00:19:37,935 --> 00:19:40,696
- WELL, HE LOOKS HEALTHY.

287
00:19:40,731 --> 00:19:44,355
- HERE, YOU WANT TO HOLD HIM?- NO, NOT RIGHT NOW.

288
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:46,495
- [baby gurgles]

289
00:19:46,530 --> 00:19:48,877
- COME ON.

290
00:19:48,911 --> 00:19:50,741
COME ON IN THE KITCHEN
WITH AUNT BILLY.

291
00:19:50,775 --> 00:19:52,777
YOU CAN HELP ME OUT.

292
00:19:52,812 --> 00:19:55,642
- OK, MAGGIE, HERE YOU GO.

293
00:19:55,677 --> 00:19:57,368
- THANK YOU.

294
00:19:57,403 --> 00:19:59,301
- SO WHAT'S YOUR POISON, BRITT?
BOURBON?

295
00:19:59,336 --> 00:20:00,647
- I'LL JUST HAVE
SOME WHITE WINE.

296
00:20:00,682 --> 00:20:02,891
- SURE.

297
00:20:02,925 --> 00:20:04,513
- WHAT ARE YOU WEARING?

298
00:20:06,688 --> 00:20:09,242
IT JUST SEEMS SO DOUR.

299
00:20:09,277 --> 00:20:11,796
- I THINK IT'S YOUR BASICSYLVIA PLATH NUMBER, ISN'T IT?

300
00:20:11,831 --> 00:20:13,660
- [laughs]
- [sighs]

301
00:20:13,695 --> 00:20:16,318
COULD WE PLEASE NOT DO THIS
TONIGHT?

302
00:20:16,353 --> 00:20:19,804
- COLOR. JUST GIVE ME
LOTS OF COLOR ANYTIME.

303
00:20:19,839 --> 00:20:22,669
WHERE DID YOU FLY IN FROM?

304
00:20:22,704 --> 00:20:24,913
- DETROIT. PHOENIX.

305
00:20:24,947 --> 00:20:26,673
I MADE A PRESENTATION
THIS MORNING

306
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:27,950
AT OMNIDEC IN SAN FRANCISCO.

307
00:20:27,985 --> 00:20:29,711
- I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU DO IT.

308
00:20:29,745 --> 00:20:32,921
I'M WORN OUT
JUST GETTING OFF THE PLANE.

309
00:20:32,955 --> 00:20:37,822
- THE PORTERS AT THE AIRPORT
SEE MORE OF HIM THAN I DO.

310
00:20:37,857 --> 00:20:41,757
- COME AND GET IT
BEFORE I CAN SKATE ON IT!

311
00:20:41,792 --> 00:20:42,896
[crickets chirping]

312
00:20:42,931 --> 00:20:44,726
- SIT UP STRAIGHT, JULIAN.

313
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:48,350
- OH, AND PLEASE DO NOT
USE YOUR SALAD FORK

314
00:20:48,385 --> 00:20:49,731
FOR THE HAM.

315
00:20:49,765 --> 00:20:53,355
- HEY, RELAX.
IT'S NOT A STEAK DINNER.

316
00:20:53,390 --> 00:20:55,426
- HE NEEDS TO LEARN
TABLE MANNERS.

317
00:20:55,461 --> 00:20:56,841
HE MIGHT BE AT A FUNCTION
SOME DAY

318
00:20:56,876 --> 00:20:58,498
WHERE IT WILL COME IN HANDY.

319
00:20:58,533 --> 00:21:00,431
- YOU DON'T KNOW WHEREHE'S GOING TO BE IN 20 YEARS.

320
00:21:00,466 --> 00:21:03,434
LET HIM BE A KID, RIGHT.

321
00:21:03,469 --> 00:21:05,712
[laughs]
- NO, NO.

322
00:21:05,747 --> 00:21:08,853
- WELL, WE CERTAINLY KNEW
WHAT YOU WERE GOING TO BE.

323
00:21:08,888 --> 00:21:10,476
YOU PRACTICALLY JUMPED
OUT OF THE WOMB,

324
00:21:10,510 --> 00:21:13,720
RAN AROUND THE CORNER
TO THE ART SUPPLY STORE.

325
00:21:13,755 --> 00:21:16,999
AND VALETTA YOU CAME OUTWITH A CHECKLIST IN YOUR HAND.

326
00:21:17,034 --> 00:21:18,967
all: [laugh]

327
00:21:19,001 --> 00:21:21,452
- I THINK SOMEONE
NEEDS A CHANGE.

328
00:21:21,487 --> 00:21:23,937
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

329
00:21:30,841 --> 00:21:32,946
- WHY DON'T YOU TAKE HIM
UPSTAIRS?

330
00:21:32,981 --> 00:21:34,879
IT'S INAPPROPRIATE.

331
00:21:34,914 --> 00:21:38,952
- HE'S A BABY.
EVERYBODY DOES IT.

332
00:21:38,987 --> 00:21:41,092
EVEN YOU, MAGGIE.

333
00:21:41,127 --> 00:21:41,955
- YOU COULD USE
THE DOWNSTAIRS BATHROOM.

334
00:21:41,990 --> 00:21:43,405
- HMM.

335
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:46,339
- OK.

336
00:21:46,374 --> 00:21:48,928
EVERYTHING UNPLEASANT
OUT OF SIGHT.

337
00:21:48,962 --> 00:21:51,310
THAT WAY, IT DOESN'T EXIST.
[baby yells]

338
00:21:54,934 --> 00:21:58,627
- SIT UP STRAIGHT, JULIAN.

339
00:21:58,662 --> 00:22:03,011
- OH, BILLY ALWAYS MAKESTHE MOST SCRUMPTIOUS COBBLERS.

340
00:22:03,045 --> 00:22:04,909
MM. BUT DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

341
00:22:04,944 --> 00:22:06,497
WE DON'T WANT HER
TO GET THE BIG HEAD.

342
00:22:06,532 --> 00:22:08,085
[laughs]

343
00:22:08,119 --> 00:22:09,811
- OUTSTANDING COBBLER, BILLY.

344
00:22:09,845 --> 00:22:12,986
- OK, HAVE ANOTHER HELPING,
KIDDO.

345
00:22:13,021 --> 00:22:15,782
OK, COFFEE COMING UP.
- LET ME HELP YOU.

346
00:22:15,817 --> 00:22:17,991
[dishes rattling]

347
00:22:18,026 --> 00:22:20,960
- MAMA, HAVE YOU GOTTENYOUR THANKSGIVING MENU TOGETHER?

348
00:22:20,994 --> 00:22:23,065
- WHAT ARE TALKING ABOUT, DEAR?

349
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:25,447
- WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO SERVE?

350
00:22:25,482 --> 00:22:28,830
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING, DARLING.

351
00:22:28,864 --> 00:22:30,866
- THANKSGIVING DINNER?

352
00:22:30,901 --> 00:22:34,456
YOU'RE COOKING IT THIS YEAR,
REMEMBER?

353
00:22:34,491 --> 00:22:37,010
- OH, WELL.

354
00:22:37,045 --> 00:22:38,874
I THINK I'D LIKE
TO GET A NEW DRESS.

355
00:22:41,843 --> 00:22:42,878
- WELL, YOU CAN DO THAT, TOO.

356
00:22:44,570 --> 00:22:48,159
- IF DINNER'S TOO MUCH
TO HANDLE, WE CAN DO IT.

357
00:22:48,194 --> 00:22:50,817
- I DON'T LIKE TO
MAKE A BIG FUSS.

358
00:22:50,852 --> 00:22:51,956
- WELL, THEN DON'T.

359
00:22:51,991 --> 00:22:55,822
- BILLY, WHAT'S FOR DESSERT?

360
00:22:55,857 --> 00:22:59,826
- MAGGIE, WE ALREADY
HAD DESSERT.

361
00:23:03,140 --> 00:23:07,006
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME MORE?

362
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:10,734
- YES, YES. I WOULD LIKE
SOME MORE, THANK YOU.

363
00:23:23,988 --> 00:23:25,887
- WHAT THE HECK WAS THAT?

364
00:23:25,921 --> 00:23:26,819
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

365
00:23:26,853 --> 00:23:28,441
- MAGGIE.

366
00:23:28,476 --> 00:23:30,581
- THE FORGETFULNESS?
- FORGETFUL?

367
00:23:30,616 --> 00:23:32,859
TODAY IN THE YARD
SHE COMPLETELY LOST IT.

368
00:23:32,894 --> 00:23:35,448
AND THEN AT DESSERT--- SHE'S OLD. WHAT DO YOU EXPECT?

369
00:23:35,483 --> 00:23:36,587
- SO YOU'RE JUST GOING TO
DISMISS THIS?

370
00:23:36,622 --> 00:23:38,071
- WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

371
00:23:38,106 --> 00:23:39,038
- I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

372
00:23:39,072 --> 00:23:40,522
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

373
00:23:40,557 --> 00:23:43,525
- ARE YOU PLANNING ON
STICKING AROUND?

374
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:46,079
BECAUSE IF YOU ARE THEN
BE MY GUEST, JUMP RIGHT IN.

375
00:23:54,950 --> 00:23:57,919
[birds tweeting]

376
00:23:57,953 --> 00:24:00,749
[laughing]

377
00:24:05,789 --> 00:24:07,273
- HOW'S DONNY?

378
00:24:07,307 --> 00:24:09,620
- HE'S GOOD.
HE'S GOOD.

379
00:24:09,655 --> 00:24:11,553
WE'VE BEEN TOGETHER
FOR SO LONG

380
00:24:11,588 --> 00:24:13,141
WE KIND OF SPEAK IN CODE.

381
00:24:13,175 --> 00:24:15,177
[laughs] NO ONE ELSE CANUNDERSTAND WHAT WE'RE SAYING,

382
00:24:15,212 --> 00:24:17,283
BUT WE CAN.

383
00:24:17,317 --> 00:24:19,458
IT'S GOOD.
IT WORKS FOR US.

384
00:24:22,771 --> 00:24:24,221
SO TELL ME THE TRUTH. HOW DOESIT FEEL TO BE BACK HOME?

385
00:24:24,255 --> 00:24:27,500
- I HAVE A RECURRING NIGHTMARE

386
00:24:27,535 --> 00:24:28,984
THAT I'LL BE STUCK HERE
FOR ETERNITY.

387
00:24:29,019 --> 00:24:32,505
- WHO WOULD HAVE THOUGHT
I'D END UP HERE.

388
00:24:32,540 --> 00:24:36,647
BUT I GET TO RAISE MY KIDS
AROUND ANIMALS AND NATURE.

389
00:24:36,682 --> 00:24:39,581
AND IT'S NOT TOO SHABBY.
WHAT CAN I SAY?

390
00:24:39,616 --> 00:24:41,549
I'VE LEARNED TO LOVE
THE SMELL OF HORSE MANURE.

391
00:24:41,583 --> 00:24:44,034
- HEY, RACE YOU TO THE POND.

392
00:24:44,068 --> 00:24:44,897
both: [laughing]

393
00:24:50,005 --> 00:24:52,870
- YA-HOO!
- HI-YA!

394
00:24:52,905 --> 00:24:54,562
[laughter]

395
00:24:54,596 --> 00:24:56,253
- COME ON!

396
00:25:03,950 --> 00:25:05,262
both: [laughing]

397
00:25:07,126 --> 00:25:11,130
- [screaming]

398
00:25:11,164 --> 00:25:13,097
WHOA! WHOA!

399
00:25:13,132 --> 00:25:16,307
both: [laughing]

400
00:25:31,599 --> 00:25:34,325
- I DID SO BEAT YOU!
- YOU DID NOT!

401
00:25:40,711 --> 00:25:42,299
[door opens]

402
00:25:43,921 --> 00:25:45,164
- MAMA?

403
00:25:45,198 --> 00:25:47,200
- OUT HERE!

404
00:25:50,065 --> 00:25:52,033
- I BROUGHT YOUR DRY CLEANING.

405
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:54,345
- OH, THANK YOU, DARLING.

406
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:57,970
DID YOU READ THE BUSINESS
SECTION THIS MORNING?

407
00:25:58,004 --> 00:25:59,040
- UH, NO.

408
00:25:59,074 --> 00:26:00,697
- BECAUSE THERE'S AN ARTICLE

409
00:26:00,731 --> 00:26:02,319
THAT MIGHT BE INTERESTING
TO JULIAN

410
00:26:02,353 --> 00:26:03,976
ABOUT SMALL TECH FIRMS.

411
00:26:06,668 --> 00:26:10,051
- UH, MAMA, I NEED TO
ASK YOU SOMETHING.

412
00:26:10,085 --> 00:26:11,328
- OF COURSE, HONEY.

413
00:26:14,676 --> 00:26:16,195
WHAT IS IT?

414
00:26:16,229 --> 00:26:18,853
- [sighs]

415
00:26:24,168 --> 00:26:27,862
WERE YOU AND DADDY...HAPPY?

416
00:26:29,657 --> 00:26:31,659
I MEAN, ALL THE TIME?

417
00:26:31,693 --> 00:26:34,627
- WELL, NO. NOT ALL THE TIME.

418
00:26:34,662 --> 00:26:38,286
WELL, WE HAD MANY
WONDERFUL MOMENTS.

419
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:40,150
WHY?

420
00:26:40,184 --> 00:26:43,256
- WELL, I THINK THAT JULIAN...

421
00:26:45,362 --> 00:26:49,262
- OH! I DON'T BELIEVE THAT.

422
00:26:49,297 --> 00:26:51,195
JULIAN LOVES YOU,

423
00:26:51,230 --> 00:26:53,094
AND HE'S AN HONEST MAN.

424
00:26:53,128 --> 00:26:55,786
DON'T YOU THINK HE'D SAYSOMETHING IF THAT WERE THE CASE?

425
00:26:55,821 --> 00:27:00,342
- [laughs]I HAVE TO PICK UP LITTLE JULIAN.

426
00:27:00,377 --> 00:27:01,412
SOCCER.

427
00:27:01,447 --> 00:27:03,104
- VALETTA?

428
00:27:03,138 --> 00:27:05,658
THERE ARE NO EASY ANSWERS.

429
00:27:05,693 --> 00:27:11,043
YOU WORK THIS OUT.
IT'S WORTH IT. TRUST ME.

430
00:27:20,431 --> 00:27:22,779
[horses snorting]

431
00:27:22,813 --> 00:27:25,126
- I'M SO EXHAUSTED
I'M CROSS-EYED.

432
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,335
- WELL, NOW YOU'RE A
DUES-PAYING MEMBER

433
00:27:27,369 --> 00:27:28,785
OF THE MOM'S CLUB.

434
00:27:28,819 --> 00:27:30,441
IT'S JUST THE WAY IT IS.

435
00:27:30,476 --> 00:27:33,030
- WHAT IF I DON'T WANT TO BE
PART OF THAT CLUB?

436
00:27:35,757 --> 00:27:38,242
- NOW, WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

437
00:27:38,277 --> 00:27:42,143
YOU'RE IN IT FOR THE LONG HAUL.
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY CHOICE.

438
00:27:42,177 --> 00:27:45,698
- I JUST FEEL LIKE I STILL HAVE
THINGS I WANT TO DO.

439
00:27:45,733 --> 00:27:47,804
- YEAH, WELL, WE ALL DO.

440
00:27:47,838 --> 00:27:51,290
- I JUST THINK MAYBE
I MADE A MISTAKE

441
00:27:51,324 --> 00:27:53,464
BRINGING A KID
INTO MY WORLD.

442
00:27:53,499 --> 00:27:56,260
- HOW HARD IS IT?

443
00:27:56,295 --> 00:27:59,367
- IT'S HARD.
[laughs]

444
00:27:59,401 --> 00:28:01,300
- WELL, CAN YOU GET BY?

445
00:28:01,334 --> 00:28:05,097
- YEAH, BARELY.

446
00:28:05,131 --> 00:28:06,823
- DOES NICHOLAS HELP YOU OUT
AT ALL?

447
00:28:06,857 --> 00:28:09,480
- IF I LET HIM.

448
00:28:09,515 --> 00:28:13,105
I'M JUST HAPPY THAT
HE LOVES BEING WITH HIS SON.

449
00:28:13,139 --> 00:28:17,281
- IF YOU GET A GUY
WITH EMOTIONAL STRENGTH,

450
00:28:17,316 --> 00:28:18,938
YOU GOT HANG ONTO HIM.

451
00:28:18,973 --> 00:28:21,320
I MEAN, YOU CAN'T
PUSH THIS ONE AWAY, BRITT.

452
00:28:25,876 --> 00:28:28,258
IT'S SO GOOD
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

453
00:28:28,292 --> 00:28:30,467
IT'S GOOD TO HAVE YOU
HERE AT HOME.

454
00:28:35,127 --> 00:28:36,991
[phone rings]

455
00:28:38,130 --> 00:28:40,304
[phone rings]

456
00:28:40,339 --> 00:28:42,859
- HELLO?
- HOW ARE YOU?

457
00:28:42,893 --> 00:28:44,826
- UNDER SIEGE.

458
00:28:44,861 --> 00:28:47,760
- YEAH, I BET.
[sighs]

459
00:28:47,795 --> 00:28:48,934
HOW'S MY BOY?

460
00:28:48,968 --> 00:28:51,281
- HE'S STINKY
I'VE BEEN TOLD.

461
00:28:51,315 --> 00:28:53,870
I'LL LET HIM TELL YOU HIMSELF.

462
00:28:53,904 --> 00:28:55,457
HEY, IT'S DADDY.

463
00:28:55,492 --> 00:28:58,564
- HI, HENRY, IT'S DADDY.

464
00:28:58,598 --> 00:29:00,462
- HE HAS NOTHING TO SAY
THIS MORNING.

465
00:29:00,497 --> 00:29:03,880
- I MISS HIM SO MUCH.

466
00:29:03,914 --> 00:29:08,229
AND YOU.

467
00:29:08,263 --> 00:29:09,471
OK, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
SAY ANYTHING.

468
00:29:09,506 --> 00:29:11,301
JUST...

469
00:29:11,335 --> 00:29:15,236
JUST KNOW THAT I'M THINKING
ABOUT YOU A LOT.

470
00:29:15,270 --> 00:29:18,549
WILL YOU CALL ME
IF YOU WANT TO TALK?

471
00:29:18,584 --> 00:29:20,448
- YEAH, I WILL.

472
00:29:20,482 --> 00:29:23,485
- OK, BYE.

473
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:25,522
- [cooing]

474
00:29:25,556 --> 00:29:27,524
- HI.

475
00:29:57,278 --> 00:29:59,245
HI.
GOOD MORNING.

476
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:02,248
- GOOD MORNING.
HOW'S HENRY?

477
00:30:02,283 --> 00:30:04,630
- TOOK HIS WHOLE BOTTLE

478
00:30:04,664 --> 00:30:07,909
LIKE A TROOPER.

479
00:30:07,944 --> 00:30:10,360
- I WAS ONCE ENGAGED
TO A LOUT

480
00:30:10,394 --> 00:30:12,845
WHO REQUIRED SEVERAL BOTTLES
A DAY.

481
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,467
[laughs]

482
00:30:14,502 --> 00:30:15,917
- HEY, THAT LOOKS NICE.

483
00:30:15,952 --> 00:30:17,919
- THANKS. IT'S A START.

484
00:30:17,954 --> 00:30:21,612
- [sighs] DID YOU EVER
WANT YOUR OWN FAMILY?

485
00:30:21,647 --> 00:30:24,857
- I HAD A FEW OFFERS
IN MY DAY.

486
00:30:24,892 --> 00:30:28,930
BUT THE TIMING
WAS ALWAYS OFF.

487
00:30:28,965 --> 00:30:33,072
THEN YOUR FATHER DIED,
AND MY LIFE CHANGED.

488
00:30:35,247 --> 00:30:36,938
- I REMEMBER YOU SPENT
THE NIGHT IN MY ROOM

489
00:30:36,973 --> 00:30:38,629
THE NIGHT HE DIED.

490
00:30:38,664 --> 00:30:41,425
- YEAH, THIS PLACEKIND OF FELL APART AFTER THAT.

491
00:30:41,460 --> 00:30:43,289
MAGS TOOK TO HER ROOM,

492
00:30:43,324 --> 00:30:45,913
AND, YOU KNOW, IN THOSE DAYS

493
00:30:45,947 --> 00:30:48,294
WE WEREN'T PARTICULARLY
FOND OF ONE ANOTHER.

494
00:30:48,329 --> 00:30:53,403
I WAS KIND OF THE BLACK SHEEP,SHOWBIZ AND ALL, YOU KNOW.

495
00:30:53,437 --> 00:30:55,405
- DO YOU MISS IT?

496
00:30:55,439 --> 00:30:57,096
- LISTEN TO ME, KIDDO,

497
00:30:57,131 --> 00:31:02,584
MY CAREER WAS JUST
ONE PEG SHORT OF HEARTBREAK.

498
00:31:02,619 --> 00:31:06,968
YEAH, I DID OK FOR
A LITTLE WHILE.

499
00:31:07,003 --> 00:31:08,659
THEN THAT WAS OVER.

500
00:31:08,694 --> 00:31:11,973
AND I GOT INTO TROUBLE,
REAL TROUBLE.

501
00:31:12,008 --> 00:31:16,322
AND ONE VERY, VERY BLEAK
THANKSGIVING

502
00:31:16,357 --> 00:31:18,946
YOUR FATHER CAME ALONG
AND BAILED ME OUT.

503
00:31:18,980 --> 00:31:23,571
THEN I LEARNED HOW TO COOKAND HOW TO BABY-SIT YOU GIRLS

504
00:31:23,605 --> 00:31:26,022
AND GOT A FAMILY IN THE BARGAIN.

505
00:31:26,056 --> 00:31:29,025
I'VE ALWAYS LOVEDTHIS HOLIDAY FOR THAT REASON.

506
00:31:29,059 --> 00:31:31,510
- YEAH, BUT DIDN'T YOU EVER
GET SICK

507
00:31:31,544 --> 00:31:33,029
OF TAKING CARE OF
ALL OF US?

508
00:31:33,063 --> 00:31:35,307
- YEAH, ALL THE TIME.

509
00:31:38,551 --> 00:31:40,726
- IS THE PLAYHOUSE STILL OPEN?

510
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:44,212
- YEAH. WELL, THE KEY'S
RIGHT THERE.

511
00:31:44,247 --> 00:31:47,664
YEAH, IT'S BEEN AGESSINCE ANYBODY'S BEEN IN THERE.

512
00:31:49,735 --> 00:31:51,633
WHY DON'T YOU GO ON.
I'LL WATCH HENRY.

513
00:31:51,668 --> 00:31:54,188
- [baby cooing]

514
00:31:54,222 --> 00:31:56,259
[plate clinks]

515
00:31:56,293 --> 00:32:04,543
♪

516
00:32:25,219 --> 00:32:27,669
[door squeaks]

517
00:32:40,406 --> 00:32:41,683
[sliding on floor]

518
00:33:01,703 --> 00:33:04,051
- BRITT?

519
00:33:04,085 --> 00:33:06,743
BRITT! ARE YOU READY
TO GO SHOPPING?

520
00:33:06,777 --> 00:33:08,262
- COME HERE.

521
00:33:10,436 --> 00:33:14,026
- OH, HEAVENS.

522
00:33:14,061 --> 00:33:16,649
BOY, THIS PLACE IS
FALLING APART.

523
00:33:16,684 --> 00:33:19,756
- LOOK AT THIS.

524
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:23,104
REMEMBER WHEN YOU PAINTED THISOF DADDY?

525
00:33:23,139 --> 00:33:27,453
- [laughs]

526
00:33:27,488 --> 00:33:28,282
WHAT WAS I THINKING?

527
00:33:32,148 --> 00:33:35,116
I NEVER WAS ANY GOOD.
- YES, YOU WERE.

528
00:33:35,151 --> 00:33:37,084
- [laughs]
OH, PLEASE.

529
00:33:37,118 --> 00:33:38,775
I SHOULD HAVE JUST ADMITTED
IT WAS A HOBBY.

530
00:33:38,809 --> 00:33:40,846
- YOU CAN SEE HE WAS
DRINKING TOO MUCH.

531
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:43,469
- WHAT A THING TO SAY.

532
00:33:43,504 --> 00:33:46,610
- COME ON, EVERYBODY KNEW
HE HAD A PROBLEM.

533
00:33:46,645 --> 00:33:48,129
WE JUST NEVER TALKED ABOUT IT.

534
00:33:48,164 --> 00:33:51,788
- OH, BRITT.

535
00:33:51,822 --> 00:33:53,134
WHY ON EARTH AREN'T YOU DRESSED?

536
00:33:53,169 --> 00:33:55,585
- IT WILL JUST TAKE A MINUTE.

537
00:33:55,619 --> 00:33:58,484
- WELL, PUT ON SOMETHING NICE.- OK.

538
00:33:58,519 --> 00:34:01,280
- AND TRY NOT TO LOOK LIKE
A GANGSTER.

539
00:34:01,315 --> 00:34:02,764
[sighs]

540
00:34:06,182 --> 00:34:09,806
[cars honking]
THAT MAKES ME SO DARN MAD.

541
00:34:12,188 --> 00:34:14,775
- YOU'RE HOLDING UP TRAFFIC.

542
00:34:14,811 --> 00:34:16,157
- THEY'RE JUST SO IMPATIENT.

543
00:34:16,192 --> 00:34:20,886
[stomping]
[brakes squeal]

544
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,612
[cars honking]
- I COULD JUST SPIT.

545
00:34:22,646 --> 00:34:24,130
- LET ME DRIVE, OK?

546
00:34:24,165 --> 00:34:26,822
- YOU'RE ALL IN SO MUCH
OF A RUSH.

547
00:34:26,857 --> 00:34:29,136
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
LEAVE IT TO ME.

548
00:34:29,170 --> 00:34:31,172
[car honking]

549
00:34:31,206 --> 00:34:33,761
WHERE THE DEVIL
IS THIS PLACE?

550
00:34:33,795 --> 00:34:35,900
IT WAS ALWAYS RIGHT HERE
ON THIRD.

551
00:34:35,935 --> 00:34:37,489
- WE'RE NOT EVEN ON THIRD.

552
00:34:37,523 --> 00:34:38,904
THIRD'S BACK THERE.
IT'S WAY BACK THERE.

553
00:34:38,938 --> 00:34:41,699
- I'VE BEEN THERE 100 TIMES.

554
00:34:41,734 --> 00:34:43,150
YOU DON'T THINK I KNOW
MY OWN TOWN?

555
00:34:43,184 --> 00:34:45,496
- WE CAN DO THIS ANOTHER DAY.

556
00:34:45,531 --> 00:34:47,568
- NO, WE'RE GOING TO DO IT
TODAY, BRITT.

557
00:34:47,601 --> 00:34:51,123
[car honking]

558
00:34:51,158 --> 00:34:52,745
[brakes squealing]

559
00:34:54,851 --> 00:34:55,817
[car zooms past]

560
00:35:01,202 --> 00:35:04,171
LOOK AROUND. YOU MIGHT FIND
SOMETHING YOU LIKE.

561
00:35:04,205 --> 00:35:06,207
- YEAH, I BROUGHT SOMETHING
WITH ME.

562
00:35:06,242 --> 00:35:07,760
- TAKE A LOOK BECAUSE
YOU MIGHT FIND SOMETHING

563
00:35:07,795 --> 00:35:09,693
YOU CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT.
[laughs]

564
00:35:09,728 --> 00:35:11,178
AND YOU NEED SOMETHING
FOR THANKSGIVING.

565
00:35:11,212 --> 00:35:13,835
- IT'S THANKSGIVING,
NOT NEW YEARS.

566
00:35:16,493 --> 00:35:17,805
- MAY I SHOW YOU SOMETHING?

567
00:35:17,839 --> 00:35:20,704
- NO, THANKS.
- YOU'RE THE WRITER.

568
00:35:20,739 --> 00:35:23,535
NO, ARTIST. YOUR MOTHERTALKS ABOUT YOU ALL THE TIME.

569
00:35:23,569 --> 00:35:26,538
- REALLY?
- OH, YES.

570
00:35:26,572 --> 00:35:28,850
THIS JUST CAME IN.

571
00:35:28,885 --> 00:35:31,508
IT'S EXQUISITE.
- NO, THANK YOU.

572
00:35:31,543 --> 00:35:34,235
- OH, THAT'S DARLING.
WHY DON'T YOU GET THAT?

573
00:35:34,270 --> 00:35:36,824
- UH, IT'S NOT REALLY ME,
THANKS.

574
00:35:36,858 --> 00:35:39,206
- OH, BUT IT'S PERFECTLY
LOVELY. MY TREAT.

575
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:41,242
- NO.
- DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

576
00:35:41,277 --> 00:35:43,969
YOU NEED SOME COLOR.

577
00:35:44,003 --> 00:35:46,213
[sighs]WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THIS ONE?

578
00:35:46,247 --> 00:35:47,559
- GOOD, BUY IT.

579
00:35:47,593 --> 00:35:50,769
- OH. [laughs]
IT'S VERY EXPENSIVE.

580
00:35:50,803 --> 00:35:53,220
- WELL, YOU SAID IT WAS
A SPECIAL OCCASION.

581
00:35:53,254 --> 00:35:54,876
- ALL RIGHT, YES.
I'LL TAKE IT.

582
00:36:00,986 --> 00:36:02,919
- WILL THERE BE ANYTHING ELSE,MRS. CALHOUN?

583
00:36:02,953 --> 00:36:05,232
- BRITT, DON'T YOU WANT
THAT DRESS?

584
00:36:05,266 --> 00:36:09,236
- IT'S REALLY NOT ME.
- YOU'LL WISH YOU HAD.

585
00:36:09,270 --> 00:36:14,241
WRAP THIS UP, MARTHA,
AND THE OTHER ONE AS WELL.

586
00:36:14,275 --> 00:36:17,934
- MAGGIE, I DON'T WANT IT.

587
00:36:17,968 --> 00:36:20,592
- WHEN YOU GET HOME,
YOU'LL CHANGE YOUR MIND.

588
00:36:20,626 --> 00:36:22,973
[laughs]

589
00:36:23,008 --> 00:36:26,253
YOU AND YOUR SISTER VALETTA
ARE NOTHING ALIKE.

590
00:36:26,287 --> 00:36:29,911
VALETTA WOULD HAVE HAD THISOUT OF HERE IN A SPLIT SECOND.

591
00:36:29,946 --> 00:36:32,293
AND, OF COURSE, HER CLOSETS
ARE ALREADY OVERFLOWING

592
00:36:32,328 --> 00:36:34,778
WITH EVERYTHING
UNDER THE SUN.

593
00:36:34,813 --> 00:36:36,953
POOR JULIAN.

594
00:36:36,987 --> 00:36:38,299
HE MUST HAVE TO WORK OVERTIME

595
00:36:38,334 --> 00:36:41,613
TO PAY FOR THE--
THE, UH...

596
00:36:41,647 --> 00:36:45,272
BUT, YOU KNOW, THE...

597
00:36:45,306 --> 00:36:47,308
[breathing heavily]

598
00:36:47,343 --> 00:36:48,723
WHAT IS THE WORD?

599
00:36:48,758 --> 00:36:50,760
- DRY CLEANING BILL?

600
00:36:50,794 --> 00:36:51,933
- YES, THAT'S IT.

601
00:36:56,628 --> 00:36:57,974
- HERE YOU GO, MRS. CALHOUN.

602
00:36:58,008 --> 00:36:59,769
IS THAT GOING TO BE
CASH OR CHARGE?

603
00:36:59,803 --> 00:37:00,942
- IT WILL BE CHARGE, DEAR.

604
00:37:06,983 --> 00:37:08,778
- MAGGIE, ARE YOU FEELING
ALL RIGHT?

605
00:37:08,812 --> 00:37:10,538
WHAT'S GOING ON?

606
00:37:10,573 --> 00:37:12,609
- I WAS JUST TRYING TO DO
SOMETHING NICE FOR YOU.

607
00:37:12,644 --> 00:37:13,714
- THAT'S NOT WHAT I'M TALKINGABOUT.

608
00:37:13,748 --> 00:37:14,784
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG.

609
00:37:14,818 --> 00:37:16,303
- OH, HERE IT COMES.

610
00:37:16,337 --> 00:37:18,028
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TAKE THIS BACK?

611
00:37:18,063 --> 00:37:20,272
- I AM NOT TALKING ABOUT
THE DRESS, AND YOU KNOW IT.

612
00:37:20,307 --> 00:37:21,825
- WELL, THEN I'M GOING TO
TAKE IT BACK.

613
00:37:21,860 --> 00:37:23,310
- NO, MAGGIE. STOP IT!
STOP!

614
00:37:23,344 --> 00:37:25,829
STOP!
[ripping]

615
00:37:35,632 --> 00:37:37,945
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

616
00:37:37,979 --> 00:37:39,912
[seat belt clicks]

617
00:37:39,947 --> 00:37:41,604
[sighs]
KEYS?

618
00:37:41,638 --> 00:37:43,778
- I DON'T MIND DRIVING.

619
00:37:43,813 --> 00:37:45,470
- I'M DRIVING. KEYS.

620
00:37:53,132 --> 00:37:55,687
[engine starts]

621
00:37:58,897 --> 00:38:01,106
- YOU USED TO BE
SUCH A HAPPY LITTLE GIRL.

622
00:38:01,140 --> 00:38:04,005
- I'M NOT A LITTLE GIRL
ANYMORE.

623
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:05,938
- AND YOU'RE NOT HAPPY EITHER.

624
00:38:05,973 --> 00:38:07,664
- I'M FINE.

625
00:38:07,699 --> 00:38:11,358
- YOU AND YOUR SISTER
ARE SO DIFFERENT.

626
00:38:11,392 --> 00:38:14,015
- BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
WE CAME FROM THE SAME PLACE.

627
00:38:14,050 --> 00:38:15,845
- I JUST KNEW YOU WERE GOING
TO GET INTO TROUBLE

628
00:38:15,879 --> 00:38:17,364
ONE OF THESE DAYS.

629
00:38:17,398 --> 00:38:19,883
YOU WERE ALWAYS OUT
ALL NIGHT LONG.

630
00:38:19,918 --> 00:38:22,369
- [scoffs] I WAS A TEENAGER
HAVING FUN.

631
00:38:22,403 --> 00:38:26,027
- I REMEMBER ONE CHARACTERWITH LONG HAIR DOWN HIS BACK,

632
00:38:26,062 --> 00:38:28,547
AND HE'D COME AROUND
ON A MOTORCYCLE.

633
00:38:28,582 --> 00:38:30,031
- [laughs] OH, YEAH,
WELL HE'S A STOCKBROKER NOW.

634
00:38:30,066 --> 00:38:31,895
ARE YOU HAPPY?

635
00:38:31,930 --> 00:38:35,036
I'M SORRY I'M SUCH
A DISAPPOINTMENT TO YOU.

636
00:38:35,071 --> 00:38:36,659
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

637
00:38:36,693 --> 00:38:37,901
- YOU KNOW EXACTLY WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

638
00:38:37,936 --> 00:38:39,662
NOTHING'S EVER GOOD ENOUGH
FOR YOU.

639
00:38:39,696 --> 00:38:42,527
- CAN'T WE HAVE AN AGREEABLE
THANKSGIVING FOR ONCE

640
00:38:42,561 --> 00:38:44,977
AND NOT DREDGE UP
A LOT OF UNPLEASANT THINGS?

641
00:38:45,012 --> 00:38:48,049
- WHY NOT?

642
00:38:48,084 --> 00:38:51,674
WE'VE BEEN DOING IT
FOR YEARS.

643
00:38:51,708 --> 00:38:53,469
[door unlocks]

644
00:38:53,503 --> 00:38:56,161
- I MADE A LIST OF THINGS
WE NEED FOR THANKSGIVING.

645
00:38:56,195 --> 00:38:58,715
YOU AND VALETTA CAN GO
TO THE STORE FOR ME.

646
00:38:58,750 --> 00:39:01,062
- FINE.

647
00:39:01,097 --> 00:39:03,375
- [sighs]
I'M DONE IN.

648
00:39:03,410 --> 00:39:04,928
- YOU WANT SOME TEA?

649
00:39:04,963 --> 00:39:07,931
- OH, THANK YOU, BILLY.
THAT WOULD BE NICE.

650
00:39:11,107 --> 00:39:14,075
ALL RIGHT, LET'S SEE
WHAT WE NEED HERE.

651
00:39:14,110 --> 00:39:16,940
[tea trickling]

652
00:39:18,459 --> 00:39:20,012
- HOW WAS HENRY?

653
00:39:20,047 --> 00:39:22,187
- OH, HE'S AN ANGEL.
HE'S SLEEPING.

654
00:39:22,221 --> 00:39:25,742
- OK, IF THEY HAVE
ANY FRESH CRANBERRIES,

655
00:39:25,777 --> 00:39:27,019
GET THOSE FOR ME.

656
00:39:27,054 --> 00:39:30,782
- OK. SEE YOU LATER.

657
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:39,100
- SOMETIMES BRITT
AND I ARE JUST--

658
00:39:39,135 --> 00:39:42,414
- SHE'S FROM A DIFFERENT PLANET
THAN YOU AND VALETTA.

659
00:39:42,449 --> 00:39:46,004
- DO I HOLD HER TO
SOME UNREASONABLE STANDARD?

660
00:39:46,038 --> 00:39:49,628
- WELL, YOU SURE HAVE BEEN
TOUGH ON HER.

661
00:39:49,663 --> 00:39:52,562
AND WITH THAT OTHER THING
HANGING OVER YOU,

662
00:39:52,597 --> 00:39:56,635
YOU NEED TO WORK THINGS OUTWITH HER BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

663
00:39:56,670 --> 00:40:00,743
HOW MUCH LONGER ARE YOU
GOING TO IGNORE THE TRUTH

664
00:40:00,777 --> 00:40:02,054
AND ADMIT THAT WE HAVE
A PROBLEM.

665
00:40:02,089 --> 00:40:04,954
- WE?

666
00:40:06,127 --> 00:40:10,062
WE DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM.
I DO.

667
00:40:10,097 --> 00:40:14,066
- LISTEN, MAGS,

668
00:40:14,101 --> 00:40:18,485
WE'VE MADE OUR PEACE,
YOU AND I, RIGHT?

669
00:40:18,519 --> 00:40:22,661
AND IF TWO OLD BAGS LIKE US
CAN GET ALONG,

670
00:40:22,696 --> 00:40:25,802
YOU CAN FIND A WAYTO GET ALONG WITH YOUR DAUGHTER.

671
00:40:25,837 --> 00:40:28,495
SHE'S A GREAT KID.
SHE'S A GOOD MOTHER.

672
00:40:28,529 --> 00:40:31,187
- I ALWAYS THOUGHT YOU WERE
OFF-CENTER.

673
00:40:31,221 --> 00:40:33,810
I SUPPOSE THAT'S WHY YOU TWOHIT IT OFF FROM THE BEGINNING.

674
00:40:33,845 --> 00:40:36,088
- I'M OFF-CENTER?

675
00:40:36,123 --> 00:40:39,229
WELL, ISN'T THAT WONDERFUL?

676
00:40:39,264 --> 00:40:41,128
- [laughs]

677
00:40:43,510 --> 00:40:45,235
- YAMS. WE NEED YAMS.

678
00:40:45,270 --> 00:40:49,688
- THERE. RIGHT THERE.
I'LL GET IT.

679
00:40:49,723 --> 00:40:53,520
- I CAN'T READ HER HANDWRITING.
OH, CRANBERRIES.

680
00:40:53,554 --> 00:40:55,798
THERE WE ARE.

681
00:40:55,832 --> 00:40:59,871
OH, THEY DON'T LOOK
VERY GOOD, DO THEY?

682
00:41:02,529 --> 00:41:05,704
- I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT MAGGIE.

683
00:41:05,739 --> 00:41:08,500
SHE HAD A LITTLE EPISODE
AT THE DRESS SHOP THIS MORNING.

684
00:41:08,535 --> 00:41:09,881
- WHAT HAPPENED?

685
00:41:14,541 --> 00:41:18,061
- SHE WAS TALKING,
AND THEN SHE JUST WENT BLANK

686
00:41:18,096 --> 00:41:21,202
AND FORGOT WHAT SHE WAS SAYING.

687
00:41:21,237 --> 00:41:22,963
THIS IS BORDERLINE ALZHEIMER'S.

688
00:41:22,997 --> 00:41:24,516
DON'T YOU THINK WE SHOULD
TALK TO A DOCTOR ABOUT THIS?

689
00:41:24,551 --> 00:41:27,139
- YOU KNOW HER.
SHE HATES DOCTORS.

690
00:41:27,174 --> 00:41:28,865
LOOK, WE ALREADY
TALKED ABOUT THIS.

691
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:30,142
SHE'S OLD.

692
00:41:30,177 --> 00:41:32,075
OLD PEOPLE HAVE LAPSES
IN MEMORY.

693
00:41:32,110 --> 00:41:34,595
[laughs] HECK, I FORGET THINGSALL THE TIME.

694
00:41:34,630 --> 00:41:36,252
- YEAH, BUT YOU DON'T FORGET
THAT YOU HAD DESSERT

695
00:41:36,286 --> 00:41:37,943
30 SECONDS AFTER
THE PLATE'S CLEARED.

696
00:41:37,978 --> 00:41:40,187
- [sighs]

697
00:41:45,192 --> 00:41:46,849
[rings]

698
00:41:46,883 --> 00:41:47,953
EXCUSE ME.

699
00:41:47,988 --> 00:41:51,232
WE NEED A BIG TURKEY.

700
00:41:51,267 --> 00:41:53,269
EVERYTHING HERE
LOOKS KIND OF PUNY.

701
00:41:53,303 --> 00:41:55,202
CAN YOU DO BETTER?
- I'LL SEE WHAT I HAVE IN BACK.

702
00:42:00,138 --> 00:42:01,864
- IF YOU WANT TO TAKE MAGGIE TO
THE DOCTOR, BE MY GUEST.

703
00:42:01,898 --> 00:42:03,141
- THERE IS SOMETHING WRONG.

704
00:42:03,175 --> 00:42:05,695
- SHE'S STRONG.

705
00:42:05,730 --> 00:42:07,214
WE'RE KEEPING AN EYE ON HER.
NOTHING'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

706
00:42:09,285 --> 00:42:11,183
- HOW'S THIS ONE?
- FREE RANGE?

707
00:42:11,218 --> 00:42:13,254
- YES, MA'AM.

708
00:42:13,289 --> 00:42:15,049
- I GUESS IT WILL
HAVE TO DO.

709
00:42:15,084 --> 00:42:17,086
[carts rattling]

710
00:42:20,123 --> 00:42:21,953
- THANK YOU.

711
00:42:23,368 --> 00:42:25,094
- WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

712
00:42:25,128 --> 00:42:26,371
- HE'S CARRYING OUR GROCERIES.

713
00:42:26,405 --> 00:42:29,685
- [laughs]
YOU THOUGHT HE WAS CUTE.

714
00:42:29,719 --> 00:42:32,239
- HEY. IF YOU'D EVER WORKED
FOR MINIMUM WAGE,

715
00:42:32,273 --> 00:42:34,172
YOU WOULD UNDERSTAND.

716
00:42:34,206 --> 00:42:35,863
- WELL, THANK GOD I DIDN'T.

717
00:42:35,898 --> 00:42:38,383
- DO YOU EVER GET
SICK OF THIS PLACE?

718
00:42:38,417 --> 00:42:40,178
NOTHING EVER CHANGES.

719
00:42:40,212 --> 00:42:42,111
- I THINK IT'S PEACEFUL.

720
00:42:42,145 --> 00:42:43,250
NOBODY'S SLEEPING
IN DOORWAYS.

721
00:42:45,217 --> 00:42:47,254
YOU HUNGRY?
- YEAH.

722
00:42:47,288 --> 00:42:48,600
- GOOD, WE'LL STOP AT THE CLUBON THE WAY HOME.

723
00:42:48,635 --> 00:42:50,395
- I'VE GOT A BETTER IDEA.

724
00:42:50,429 --> 00:42:52,052
LET'S GET THESE HOME FIRST.

725
00:42:54,295 --> 00:42:55,262
[country music playing]
[patrons chatting]

726
00:42:55,296 --> 00:42:57,229
[lighter flicks]

727
00:43:04,374 --> 00:43:05,928
- IT'S A DUMP.

728
00:43:05,962 --> 00:43:09,310
- THINK OF IT AS CHARACTER.

729
00:43:09,345 --> 00:43:11,934
- I HOPE WE DON'T PICK UP
SOME AIRBORNE DISEASE.

730
00:43:11,968 --> 00:43:15,282
- HEY, I HAD SOME GREAT TIMESIN HERE, AND I'M ALIVE.

731
00:43:15,316 --> 00:43:18,630
- I THINK I'D HAVE MY DOCTORDO A FULL WORK-UP IF I WERE YOU.

732
00:43:18,665 --> 00:43:20,252
- [laughs lightly]

733
00:43:23,152 --> 00:43:25,292
SEE THAT BOOTH OVER THERE?

734
00:43:25,326 --> 00:43:29,434
I USED TO MAKE OUT
WITH JOHN HARDING IN THERE.

735
00:43:29,468 --> 00:43:32,264
MY LIPS WERE RAW
BY THE TIME I GOT HOME.

736
00:43:32,299 --> 00:43:34,232
- NOW THERE'S AN APPEALING
MEMORY.

737
00:43:34,266 --> 00:43:36,234
- [laughs]

738
00:43:36,268 --> 00:43:39,686
EXCUSE ME, COULD WE HAVE
TWO CHEESEBURGERS,

739
00:43:39,720 --> 00:43:43,068
EVERYTHING ON 'EM,AND A COUPLE SHOTS OF TEQUILA.

740
00:43:43,103 --> 00:43:44,449
- NO ONIONS FOR ME.

741
00:43:44,483 --> 00:43:46,762
- EVERYTHING, PLEASE.

742
00:43:49,488 --> 00:43:51,318
- YOU'VE CLEARLY LED
A MORE BOHEMIAN LIFESTYLE.

743
00:43:51,352 --> 00:43:54,286
- WELL, IT WASN'T
THE COUNTRY CLUB.

744
00:44:13,443 --> 00:44:15,480
- MY LIFESTYLE MAY NOT
APPEAL TO YOU,

745
00:44:15,514 --> 00:44:18,345
BUT SOMEBODY HAD TO BE AT HOMETAKING CARE OF MAMA.

746
00:44:18,379 --> 00:44:21,003
- [sighs] SO TELL MEWHAT'S GOING ON WITH HER NOW.

747
00:44:21,037 --> 00:44:26,180
- EXCUSE ME.
TWO MORE, PLEASE.

748
00:44:28,355 --> 00:44:31,461
I CAN HANDLE IT.
- ALL RIGHT.

749
00:44:31,496 --> 00:44:34,361
- I'M GOING TO BE HONEST.

750
00:44:34,395 --> 00:44:36,363
SOMETIMES I GET TIRED OFBEING THE ONE TO LOOK AFTER HER.

751
00:44:38,227 --> 00:44:40,263
WHY SHOULD I DO IT ALL?

752
00:44:40,298 --> 00:44:43,335
- BECAUSE I DON'T LIVE HERE.

753
00:44:53,449 --> 00:44:56,314
[dog barking in distance]

754
00:44:56,348 --> 00:44:59,144
[cooing]

755
00:45:16,506 --> 00:45:18,370
[gurgles]

756
00:45:30,451 --> 00:45:33,109
[birds tweeting]

757
00:45:34,593 --> 00:45:37,079
- BRITT? BRITT.

758
00:45:37,113 --> 00:45:39,150
YOU HAVE A LONG DISTANCE
PHONE CALL.

759
00:45:39,184 --> 00:45:42,222
[phone beeps]
- HELLO?

760
00:45:42,256 --> 00:45:44,293
- HOW ARE THINGS BACK HOME?

761
00:45:44,327 --> 00:45:46,398
- WEIRD. HOW ARE YOU?

762
00:45:46,433 --> 00:45:48,331
- WE HEARD FROM THE FOUNDATION.

763
00:45:48,366 --> 00:45:51,265
- AND?

764
00:45:51,300 --> 00:45:53,095
- YOU'VE GOT THE GRANT.

765
00:45:53,129 --> 00:45:56,236
- [screams and laughs]

766
00:45:56,270 --> 00:45:57,789
- ARE YOU OK?

767
00:45:57,824 --> 00:46:00,343
- I GOT THE GRANT.
I GOT IT! I GOT IT!

768
00:46:00,378 --> 00:46:03,208
- ARE YOU THERE? BRITT?
- OH!

769
00:46:03,243 --> 00:46:04,485
HELLO? HELLO?

770
00:46:04,520 --> 00:46:06,108
- LOOK, HAVE
A HAPPY THANKSGIVING.

771
00:46:06,142 --> 00:46:07,592
YOU DESERVE IT.

772
00:46:07,626 --> 00:46:09,456
WE'LL GO OVER THE DETAILS
WHEN YOU GET BACK.

773
00:46:09,490 --> 00:46:11,285
- OK. THANKS!

774
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:12,459
[clicks off phone]

775
00:46:12,493 --> 00:46:14,392
- OH...
- I GOT THE GRANT.

776
00:46:14,426 --> 00:46:17,222
- THAT'S MY GIRL.
- [laughs]

777
00:46:17,257 --> 00:46:19,846
- [laughs]

778
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:22,814
- OH! OH, DON'T TELL ANYBODY.I WANT IT TO BE A BIG SURPRISE.

779
00:46:22,849 --> 00:46:24,264
I'LL SAVE IT FOR DINNER.

780
00:46:24,298 --> 00:46:26,887
- OK. BUT I'M NOT SURPRISED.

781
00:46:26,922 --> 00:46:30,132
- OH...

782
00:46:30,166 --> 00:46:33,307
[lawnmower motor]

783
00:46:35,309 --> 00:46:37,484
[buzzing]

784
00:46:37,518 --> 00:46:39,141
- IT DOESN'T NEED
TO GO THAT WAY.

785
00:46:39,175 --> 00:46:40,452
IT JUST NEEDS TO GO THIS WAY.

786
00:46:40,487 --> 00:46:42,213
- YOU KNOW, MY CAR AUTOMATICALLY

787
00:46:42,247 --> 00:46:43,835
HEADS STRAIGHT FOR
YOUR MOTHER'S HOUSE THESE DAYS.

788
00:46:43,870 --> 00:46:46,113
YOU'RE ALWAYS HERE.

789
00:46:46,148 --> 00:46:47,874
- YOU LOOK SMUG.

790
00:46:47,908 --> 00:46:50,152
- YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW.
- HOW DID IT GO?

791
00:46:50,186 --> 00:46:51,463
[kissing sounds]

792
00:46:53,293 --> 00:46:55,433
JULIAN! COME ON, TELL ME.

793
00:46:55,467 --> 00:46:59,540
- OK, OK. I DID IT.
I SOLD MY IDEA TO OMNIDEC.

794
00:46:59,575 --> 00:47:02,440
- THAT'S FANTASTIC!
- IT GETS BETTER.

795
00:47:02,474 --> 00:47:04,994
THEY WANT TO BUY ME OUT.
- WHAT?

796
00:47:05,029 --> 00:47:06,858
- AND THEY WANT ME TO STAY ONAND RUN THE NEW COMPANY.

797
00:47:06,893 --> 00:47:08,653
- ARE YOU GOING TO DO IT?

798
00:47:08,687 --> 00:47:11,898
- IT WOULD BE HARD TO PASS UP.WE'D BE SET FOR LIFE.

799
00:47:11,932 --> 00:47:14,141
- BUT IS THIS GOING TO MEAN
MORE TIME ON THE ROAD?

800
00:47:14,176 --> 00:47:16,972
- FOR A WHILE.

801
00:47:19,560 --> 00:47:21,286
- [sighs]

802
00:47:21,321 --> 00:47:26,326
ALL THIS TIME ON THE ROAD,

803
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:27,465
IT'S HARD ON US.

804
00:47:27,499 --> 00:47:32,504
- VALETTA, THIS IS A GOOD THING.

805
00:47:32,539 --> 00:47:35,162
MY WORK, IT'S FOR BOTH OF US.

806
00:47:35,197 --> 00:47:36,508
- I MISS YOU.

807
00:48:05,365 --> 00:48:07,505
- [sighs]

808
00:48:26,041 --> 00:48:28,043
[sighs]

809
00:48:33,427 --> 00:48:36,258
[laughs]

810
00:48:36,292 --> 00:48:38,260
- WHO'S IN THERE?

811
00:48:38,294 --> 00:48:39,571
- IT'S JUST ME.

812
00:48:49,305 --> 00:48:52,067
- WHAT THE DEVIL ARE YOU
DOING IN HERE?

813
00:48:53,689 --> 00:48:55,656
YOU'LL GET FILTHY
AS ALL GET OUT.

814
00:48:55,691 --> 00:48:58,556
- I WAS JUST LOOKING FOR
SOME OF OUR OLD TOYS.

815
00:48:58,590 --> 00:49:00,627
I THOUGHT HENRY
COULD USE THEM.

816
00:49:00,661 --> 00:49:02,284
- WHAT WERE YOU LAUGHING ABOUT?

817
00:49:02,318 --> 00:49:05,597
- THIS.

818
00:49:07,461 --> 00:49:09,981
- OH!
[laughs]

819
00:49:10,016 --> 00:49:11,569
- YOU SHOULD HAVE BURNED THAT.

820
00:49:11,603 --> 00:49:13,640
- WE SHOULD KEEP IT
FOR YOUR SON.

821
00:49:13,674 --> 00:49:15,504
- DON'T YOU DARE SHOW THAT
TO ANYBODY.

822
00:49:15,538 --> 00:49:18,645
- [laughs]
- GIVE ME THAT.

823
00:49:18,679 --> 00:49:22,580
- YOU KNOW, YOUR FATHER
TOOK THAT ON VACATION.

824
00:49:22,614 --> 00:49:24,651
WE WERE IN SAN DIEGO.

825
00:49:26,722 --> 00:49:28,448
- IT SEEMS LIKE HE DIED
A LONG TIME AGO.

826
00:49:28,482 --> 00:49:32,279
- NOT FOR ME.

827
00:49:32,314 --> 00:49:36,663
- EVEN WHEN I LOOK AT
HIS PICTURE, IT'S...

828
00:49:36,697 --> 00:49:38,665
IT'S HARD FOR ME
TO REMEMBER HIM.

829
00:49:38,699 --> 00:49:42,772
- HE WAS SO THRILLED
WHEN YOU CAME ALONG.

830
00:49:42,807 --> 00:49:44,636
WE DIDN'T EXPECT
TO HAVE ANOTHER CHILD.

831
00:49:44,671 --> 00:49:46,673
HE THOUGHT YOU WERE
A TREASURE.

832
00:49:50,056 --> 00:49:51,781
OH, LET ME SEE THAT SILLY THING.

833
00:49:51,816 --> 00:49:54,474
- YEAH, YOU PAID MONEY
FOR THIS?

834
00:49:54,508 --> 00:49:57,304
- I BEG YOUR PARDON.

835
00:49:57,339 --> 00:49:59,410
I WAS THE RAGE OF
THE THANKSGIVING BALL

836
00:49:59,444 --> 00:50:01,653
AT THE CLUB.

837
00:50:01,688 --> 00:50:03,483
- UH-HUH.

838
00:50:07,349 --> 00:50:09,730
- OH.

839
00:50:09,765 --> 00:50:12,354
IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

840
00:50:29,888 --> 00:50:33,754
- VALETTA, WHAT ARE YOU DOINGOUT HERE?

841
00:50:33,789 --> 00:50:37,689
- UM, I'M JUST...

842
00:50:37,724 --> 00:50:39,691
WAITING FOR THE LANDSCAPERS.

843
00:50:39,726 --> 00:50:42,625
THEY'RE-- THEY'RE NOT FINISHED.

844
00:50:42,660 --> 00:50:44,696
- I TALKED TO MERLE
AND CONNIE.

845
00:50:44,731 --> 00:50:47,320
THEY SAID THEY'RE GOING
TO BE HERE FOR THANKSGIVING.

846
00:50:47,354 --> 00:50:48,666
- THAT'S GOOD.

847
00:50:52,359 --> 00:50:53,533
[chair leg scrapes]

848
00:50:57,399 --> 00:50:58,572
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

849
00:51:01,748 --> 00:51:04,406
- I'M JUST NOT SURE
HOW IT'S GOING TO TURN OUT.

850
00:51:07,616 --> 00:51:10,722
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE TO TELL
BRITT ABOUT MAMA, YOU KNOW.

851
00:51:10,757 --> 00:51:14,416
- THE RIGHT TIME
WILL PRESENT ITSELF.

852
00:51:15,727 --> 00:51:18,903
- IT'S GOING TO BE HARD.

853
00:51:18,937 --> 00:51:22,113
I'M NOT SURE IF
I'M READY FOR IT.

854
00:51:22,148 --> 00:51:25,875
- YOU JUST KEEP ONLOVING YOUR MOTHER SWEETHEART.

855
00:51:25,910 --> 00:51:28,430
THAT'S ALL YOU NEED TO
CONCENTRATE ON.

856
00:51:31,433 --> 00:51:33,711
- I'LL HANDLE IT.

857
00:51:36,403 --> 00:51:38,750
[crickets chirping]

858
00:51:45,723 --> 00:51:47,759
- [sighs]

859
00:52:02,188 --> 00:52:05,432
MMM. I'VE REALLY MISSED
YOUR CHICKEN, BILLY.

860
00:52:05,467 --> 00:52:07,745
- OOH, WAIT 'TIL YOU SEE
WHAT'S FOR DESSERT.

861
00:52:12,750 --> 00:52:14,786
- I HAD SOME GOOD NEWS TODAY.

862
00:52:17,789 --> 00:52:20,447
I FOUND OUT THAT, UM,

863
00:52:20,482 --> 00:52:21,931
I'M THE RECIPIENT OF

864
00:52:21,966 --> 00:52:25,211
THE ARTIST ACADEMY
FOUNDATION GRANT.

865
00:52:25,245 --> 00:52:26,764
- HMM.

866
00:52:28,766 --> 00:52:31,631
- CONGRATULATIONS.
- THAT'S GREAT.

867
00:52:31,665 --> 00:52:33,909
- IT'S AN IMPORTANT GROUP
OF PEOPLE

868
00:52:33,943 --> 00:52:35,738
WHO RECOGNIZE ARTISTS
THEY BELIEVE

869
00:52:35,773 --> 00:52:37,740
SHOW EXCEPTIONAL PROMISE.

870
00:52:37,775 --> 00:52:40,364
YOU KNOW, BIG WIGS!

871
00:52:40,398 --> 00:52:43,643
- WELL, I'M SURE EVERYONE HERE'SVERY PLEASED FOR YOU, BRITT.

872
00:52:45,714 --> 00:52:48,820
HOW DOES IT WORK EXACTLY?
DO THEY GIVE YOU MONEY?

873
00:52:48,855 --> 00:52:50,719
- THERE'S MONEY INVOLVED, YEAH.

874
00:52:50,753 --> 00:52:51,892
- CAN YOU LIVE ON IT?

875
00:52:51,927 --> 00:52:53,756
- FOR A WHILE.

876
00:52:53,791 --> 00:52:55,448
- REALLY?

877
00:52:55,482 --> 00:52:58,209
ENOUGH FOR RENT AND FOOD
AND EVERYTHING?

878
00:52:58,244 --> 00:53:00,763
- WELL, I DON'T NEED THAT MUCH.
THERE'S ENOUGH FOR HENRY.

879
00:53:00,798 --> 00:53:02,455
- WELL, HOPEFULLY YOU'LL SELL

880
00:53:02,489 --> 00:53:05,975
SOME OF YOUR OTHER PIECES
AS WELL.

881
00:53:06,010 --> 00:53:07,839
- WELL, AS LONG AS WE'RE
PASSING OUT GOOD NEWS,

882
00:53:07,874 --> 00:53:08,806
I HAVE SOME.

883
00:53:10,946 --> 00:53:12,844
I SOLD MY COMPANY TODAY.

884
00:53:12,879 --> 00:53:17,228
- OH, JULIAN.
CONGRATULATIONS.

885
00:53:17,263 --> 00:53:20,231
- I ALWAYS KNEW ALL THATFLYING AROUND LIKE A BOOMERANG

886
00:53:20,266 --> 00:53:22,682
WOULD SOONER OR LATER
PAY OFF IN A BIG WAY.

887
00:53:22,716 --> 00:53:23,959
- [laughs]

888
00:53:23,993 --> 00:53:25,409
- HE CERTAINLY HAS
PAID HIS DUES.

889
00:53:25,443 --> 00:53:27,997
- OH, I WISH YOUR FATHER
WAS HERE, GIRLS.

890
00:53:28,032 --> 00:53:31,794
HE'D BE TICKLED TO DEATH
FOR YOU, JULIAN.

891
00:53:31,829 --> 00:53:34,038
HERE'S TO MY SUCCESSFUL
CHILDREN.

892
00:53:34,072 --> 00:53:35,557
- HERE, HERE.

893
00:53:38,560 --> 00:53:39,940
[pats leg]

894
00:53:39,975 --> 00:53:41,735
- [laughs]

895
00:53:54,092 --> 00:53:55,715
- YOU STILL UP?

896
00:53:59,719 --> 00:54:00,858
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

897
00:54:02,929 --> 00:54:04,862
- WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO
TO GET HER ATTENTION?

898
00:54:07,934 --> 00:54:10,833
BECAUSE SOMETIMES
I HATE HER.

899
00:54:10,868 --> 00:54:13,595
- OH, PLEASE DON'T SAY THAT.

900
00:54:21,119 --> 00:54:25,745
YOU KNOW, WE ALL HAVE
OUR FAULTS, INCLUDING YOU.

901
00:54:27,609 --> 00:54:30,025
TOMORROW'S RUNNING OUT.

902
00:54:30,059 --> 00:54:33,649
YOU NEED TO MAKE YOUR PEACE
WHILE THERE'S STILL TIME.

903
00:54:33,684 --> 00:54:36,065
- HOW? HMM?

904
00:54:36,100 --> 00:54:37,929
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO DO THAT.

905
00:54:37,964 --> 00:54:41,795
- JUST OFFER HER
WHAT YOU'RE BEST AT.

906
00:54:41,830 --> 00:54:44,936
- [sniffs]
[baby whines]

907
00:54:44,971 --> 00:54:47,318
- WY DON'T YOU LET ME
PUT HENRY TO BED.

908
00:54:47,353 --> 00:54:49,631
YOU WORK A WHILE.
YOU'LL PROBABLY FEEL BETTER.

909
00:54:51,943 --> 00:54:54,118
COME ON, HENRY.

910
00:54:54,152 --> 00:54:56,672
- GOODNIGHT, BABY.

911
00:54:56,707 --> 00:54:58,433
- OH.

912
00:55:14,587 --> 00:55:19,902
[rain and thunder]

913
00:55:42,408 --> 00:55:43,926
[thuds]

914
00:56:18,029 --> 00:56:20,963
[thunder rolls]

915
00:56:34,943 --> 00:56:36,703
[laughs lightly]

916
00:56:46,817 --> 00:56:49,992
- MAGGIE! MAGGIE!

917
00:56:58,069 --> 00:56:59,899
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

918
00:56:59,933 --> 00:57:02,522
- I CAN'T FIND MY HAIR BRUSH.

919
00:57:05,042 --> 00:57:07,734
- MAGGIE.

920
00:57:09,149 --> 00:57:10,944
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY YARD?

921
00:57:12,981 --> 00:57:15,086
LEAVE ME ALONE.
LEAVE ME ALONE!

922
00:57:15,121 --> 00:57:18,055
LEAVE ME ALONE!
- IT'S ME. IT'S ME!

923
00:57:18,089 --> 00:57:20,989
IT'S BRITT. IT'S ME, MAMA.
- [sobbing]

924
00:57:21,023 --> 00:57:23,750
- MAMA.
- [crying]

925
00:57:23,785 --> 00:57:26,063
- COME HERE.

926
00:57:26,097 --> 00:57:29,031
STEP UP, STEP UP.
THERE YOU GO.

927
00:57:29,066 --> 00:57:30,895
GOOD. COME ON.

928
00:57:30,930 --> 00:57:33,795
ALL RIGHT.
- [sobbing]

929
00:57:33,829 --> 00:57:37,764
ARE WE GOING TO FIND CHARLIE?

930
00:57:37,799 --> 00:57:41,941
- NO. DADDY'S NOT OUT THERE.

931
00:57:44,288 --> 00:57:45,910
OK.

932
00:58:02,306 --> 00:58:04,619
[thunder rolls]

933
00:58:31,749 --> 00:58:33,924
[distant thunder]

934
00:58:36,167 --> 00:58:37,997
- HOW'D I GET OUT HERE?

935
00:58:40,827 --> 00:58:42,001
[sighs]

936
00:58:44,175 --> 00:58:45,591
[sighs]

937
00:58:45,625 --> 00:58:48,110
- SO ARE WE GOING TO
TALK ABOUT THIS?

938
00:58:50,734 --> 00:58:53,115
- [sighs]

939
00:58:53,150 --> 00:58:56,015
THE DOCTOR SAYS THAT
I HAVE...

940
00:58:57,982 --> 00:59:01,158
YOU KNOW, I'M LOSING IT.

